Decided I would try a few of the local Ethiopian restaurants in my neighborhood since I always go into DC when I want Ethiopian food. Was so disappointed and disgusted with the service/food at Langano's. Firstly, we were seated and forgotten about to the point where we were getting ready to walk out (and I wish we had) but then our server showed up and ask if we were ready. We ordered the vegetarian platter along with some beef tips. The food arrived cold...some of the sides seemed chilled almost. Now I've had Ethiopian food before, as a matter of fact it's one of my favorites, and never before have I been served cold food and told it was customary when I finally tracked down a server. After going back and forth, explaining that I know the salad and beets should be cold but the entire platter being cold was unacceptable, the server offered to bring me two more servings of my choice that they would heat. I told her I don't want just two, I want my entire meal to be appetizing, she left again to speak to her manager. After another lengthy wait,  the manager comes over and also says that this is the way Abbisha people eat their veggies. I told her I have eaten at many Ethiopian restaurants and never before have I experienced cold food as traditional. She returned with small plates to take my sides and heat them. At this point the entire experience and our appetites were ruined, but she was trying to make us happy, which is the only reason for the one star. Honestly I think they should not have even charged us for this experience or at least the bill should have been discounted, but I do get that they have to make a living, and so the full bill was presented and was paid, and a 15% tip was left. My daughter took one last sip of her water while we were taking care of the bill and to everyone's disgust there was a long hair stuck to the inside of the glass (gag) not floating; firmly attached to a substance on the inside of the glass. Despite the managers last ditched attempt to rectify the cold food situation the hair clinging to the inside of the glass put the whole horrible experience over the top. I will never return to this establishment. Poor service, cold food, unsanitary. Three thumbs down.

Fantastic food!  Cooked to order and it sure takes a while, so grab some appetizer to eat and plan on sitting and relaxing, or get something from their nice-sized and well-stocked bar.  The food is worth the wait.  There are probably only about 12 tables, a mix of 2 and 4 person ones.  An Ethiopian friend said it is a famous sports bar for his community.  Almost all the diners seemed to be Ethiopian or at least African, meaning recent immigrants to the US.  There were a few couples but mostly single males.  Half were staring at the huge screen polo game in the "right rear corner" which was also my view (sitting with my back to the front window). But then half the guys seemed to be staring either at the front door or over my head or ... I wasn't sure. But halfway through dinner I realized there was another large-screen tv behind me, and that the endless recorded singing by some young contemporary Ethiopian woman was actually a music video at which they were googly-eyed staring!
